%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G3.1+G3.2: 3WHS negotiation, both endpoints
AccECN-capable (tcpEcnMode="accecn"). The client's SYN uses the SEWA
codepoint (ECE=CWR=AE=1, RFC 3168's classic-ECN-willing pattern plus the AE
bit); the server recognizes it as an AccECN request (not classic -- G3.2's
AccECN check runs before the classic ECE&&CWR check) and replies with the
SW. accept codepoint (ECE=0, CWR=1, AE=0); the client's G3.1 decode logic
matches (0,1,0) and marks the connection AccECN-negotiated.

Tested via a real two-INET-instance handshake, not hand-injected packets:
G3.1 (client SYN-ACK decode) and G3.2 (server SYN accept/reflect) are
tightly coupled -- the client's decode logic can only be meaningfully
exercised against a real AccECN-aware server's actual reply, so both
commits' code landed together before this test was written.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.*_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's SYN: SEWA (SYN+ECE+CWR+AE), requesting AccECN. Rendered "S E W N" -- AE renders
%# as "N" (its RFC 3540 NS heritage), not "A", to avoid colliding with the ACK flag's "A".
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S E W N 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's SYN-ACK: SW. (SYN+ACK+CWR only) -- the AccECN accept codepoint.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S W 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN received
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN-ACK sent... AccECN is enabled
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN-setup SYN-ACK received... AccECN is enabled.
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
